<section id="sect-00005">
  <title>Conversion Factors</title>
  <para id="para-00007">Conversion between metric system units routinely occurs when preparing to administer drugs to patients. There are six common units of measurement used for drug administration based on volume (liter and milliliter) and weight (kilogram, gram, milligram, and microgram). Each unit differs from the next by 1000 (<link target-id="table_02_02"/>).
  </para>
