  <section id="sect-00009">
    <title>Ratio and Proportion Method</title>
    <para id="para-00012">The ratio and proportion method uses a linear equation to solve the dosage calculation problem.</para>

    <equation id="eq-00004">
      <m:math display="block">
        <m:mrow>
          <m:mtable>
            <m:mtr>
              <m:mtd columnalign="left"><m:mi>K</m:mi><m:mi>R</m:mi><m:mo>:</m:mo><m:mi>U</m:mi><m:mi>R</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mi>X</m:mi></m:mtd>
              <m:mtd columnalign="left"><m:mi>K</m:mi><m:mi>R</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mtext>Known ratio (available)</m:mtext></m:mtd>
            </m:mtr>
            <m:mtr>
              <m:mtd/>
              <m:mtd columnalign="left"><m:mi>U</m:mi><m:mi>R</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mtext>Unknown ratio (dose ordered)</m:mtext></m:mtd>
          </m:mtr>
          <m:mtr>
            <m:mtd/>
              <m:mtd columnalign="left"><m:mi>X</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mtext>Amount to be administered to the patient</m:mtext></m:mtd>
            </m:mtr>
          </m:mtable>
        </m:mrow>
      </m:math>
    </equation>
    
    <list list-type="enumerated" id="list-00005">
      <item>Write the known ratio (dosage strength from drug label and units of measurement).</item>
      <item>Write the unknown ratio (the ordered dose and the unknown amount to be administered to the patient).</item>
      <item>Check the units of measurement to make sure they are the same (e.g., mg:mg). Note that if they are not the same, then you must convert them to the same unit of measurement.</item>
      <item>Solve for <m:math><m:mi>X</m:mi></m:math> (the amount calculated to be administered to the patient) by multiplying the means and the extremes. (Work only with the numbers and not the units of measurement.) Clear the <m:math><m:mi>X</m:mi></m:math> by dividing both sides of the equation by the number in front of the <m:math><m:mi>X</m:mi></m:math> and solve for <m:math><m:mi>X</m:mi></m:math>.
      </item>
    </list>
    
    <list list-type="bulleted" bullet-style="none" id="list-00006">
      <title>Example</title>
      <item>Order: Lisinopril 10 mg po bid</item>
      <item>Available: Lisinopril 2.5 mg</item>
      <item>How many tablets should the patient receive per dose?</item>
    </list>
    
        <figure id="pharma_fig_02_05_004">
          <media alt="Alt text here.">
            <image mime-type="png" src="../../media/pharma_fig_02_05_004.png"/>
          </media>
          <caption>TBC / credit: TBC (placeholder image)
          </caption>
        </figure>
    
      <equation id="eq-00005">
        <m:math display="block">
          <m:mtable>
            <m:mtr>
              <m:mtd columnalign="right"><m:mi>K</m:mi><m:mi>R</m:mi><m:mo>:</m:mo><m:mi>U</m:mi><m:mi>R</m:mi></m:mtd>
              <m:mtd><m:mo>=</m:mo></m:mtd>
              <m:mtd columnalign="left"><m:mi>X</m:mi></m:mtd>
            </m:mtr>
            <m:mtr>
              <m:mtd columnalign="right"><m:mrow><m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mo>.</m:mo><m:mn>5</m:mn><m:mi>m</m:mi><m:mi>g</m:mi><m:mo>:</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mtext>tablet</m:mtext><m:mo>:</m:mo><m:mn>10</m:mn><m:mi>m</m:mi><m:mi>g</m:mi><m:mo>:</m:mo><m:mi>X</m:mi><m:mtext>tablets</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mtd>
