</section>
      <section id="sect-00010">
        <title>Dimensional Analysis Method</title>
        <para id="para-00013">Dimensional analysis uses a series of equivalent measurements to change one unit of measurement to another to solve a problem. This method uses equivalent measurements that are set up as a series of fractions, called conversion factors that are used to cancel unnecessary units of measurements, leaving only the desired answer.</para>
        <para id="para-00014"/>
      </section>
      
      <section id="sect-00011">
        <title>Body Weight Method</title>
        <para id="para-00015">The body weight method allows dosage calculation for individualization. This method is commonly seen with medications that have a narrow therapeutic index, drugs that are being adjusted due to the individual’s ability to metabolize the drug, and also with pediatric patients.
        </para>

        <table id="table_02_04" summary="Alt text here.">
          <tgroup cols="3">
            <thead>
              <row>
                <entry>Formula Method</entry>
                <entry>Ratio Proportion</entry>
                <entry>Dimensional Analysis</entry>
              </row>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <row>
                <entry>
                  <m:math>
                    <m:mfrac>
                      <m:mrow><m:mtext>D (desired dose)</m:mtext></m:mrow>
                      <m:mrow><m:mtext>H (dose available)</m:mtext></m:mrow>
                    </m:mfrac>
                    <m:mo>×</m:mo>
                    <m:mtext>Volume</m:mtext><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mi>A</m:mi>
                  </m:math>
                </entry>
                <entry>
                  <m:math>
                    <m:mi>K</m:mi><m:mi>R</m:mi><m:mtext> (known ratio)</m:mtext><m:mo>:</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>U</m:mi><m:mi>R</m:mi><m:mtext> (unknown ratio)</m:mtext>
                    <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>X</m:mi><m:mtext> (amount calculated to be administered)</m:mtext>
                  </m:math>
                </entry>
                <entry>
                  <m:math>
                    <m:mi>O</m:mi><m:mi>A</m:mi><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mi>D</m:mi><m:mi>S</m:mi>
                    <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>D</m:mi><m:mi>A</m:mi><m:mtext> (desired amount calculated to be administered to patient)</m:mtext>
                  </m:math>
                </entry>
              </row>
              <row>
                <entry>
                  <m:math>
                    <m:mtable frame="none">
                      <m:mtr>
                        <m:mtd><m:mi>A</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mtext>Amount calculated to be administered to the patient</m:mtext></m:mtd>
                      </m:mtr>
